Pre-Requisites(if not exists):
============================
Download and Install Java
Configure environmental variables
Download and Install IDE either Eclipse/IntelliJ



Steps:
======================
Enter command git clone "repository name" in your terminal
Navigate to the repository
Now, Navigate to the "drivers" folder of the repository(Its the place where selenium grid jars are placed)
Run this command: java -jar selenium-server-4.6.0.jar hub (To start the hub)
Now, Run this command: java -Dwebdriver.chrome.driver=“driverpath” -jar selenium-server-4.6.0.jar node  hub (To start the node and connect with the hub on same machine)
Open Project in Eclipse IDE
Start Running Project
